docs.abstract: The president’s response to the coronavirus that killed more than 100,000 people was lethargic and ineffective. But when it came to anti-racism protesters, it was time to call in the troops.
docs.snippet: The president’s response to the coronavirus that killed more than 100,000 people was lethargic and ineffective. But when it came to anti-racism protesters, it was time to call in the troops.
docs.lead_paragraph: For two decades, the United States has repeatedly made the mistake of over-relying on the military toolbox to try to solve intractable problems — particularly in Afghanistan and Iraq — without adequately relying on diplomacy. Now President Trump wants to repeat the mistake at home.

headline.main: Trump Uses the Military to Prove His Manhood

docs.abstract: Scholars said they would not hold classes or lectures on Wednesday, and leading journals and scientific associations said they would not announce most breakthroughs.
docs.snippet: Scholars said they would not hold classes or lectures on Wednesday, and leading journals and scientific associations said they would not announce most breakthroughs.
docs.lead_paragraph: Galvanized by the reaction to the killing of George Floyd and continued reports that minority researchers feel marginalized and disrespected, almost 6,000 scientists and academicians said they would participate in a one-day strike on Wednesday.

headline.main: For a Day, Scientists Pause Science to Confront Racism
headline.print_headline: No Classes, No Meetings, No Reports: To Battle Racism, Scientists Halt Science for a Day

docs.abstract: The pastor, Leon K. McCray, had called to report that five white people were threatening him and taunting him with racial slurs at an apartment complex he owns. He ended up in custody.
docs.snippet: The pastor, Leon K. McCray, had called to report that five white people were threatening him and taunting him with racial slurs at an apartment complex he owns. He ended up in custody.
docs.lead_paragraph: A Virginia sheriff has apologized to a black pastor who was arrested earlier this month after he called 911 to report that a group of white people were trespassing on his property and taunting him with racial slurs.

headline.main: Virginia Sheriff Apologizes for Arrest of Black Pastor Who Called 911
headline.print_headline: Black Pastor Receives Apology for Arrest

docs.abstract: Amid widespread protests against police brutality and the coronavirus pandemic, a determined electorate pushed turnout past 2016 levels.
docs.snippet: Amid widespread protests against police brutality and the coronavirus pandemic, a determined electorate pushed turnout past 2016 levels.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the nation remained gripped by widespread protests against police brutality and systemic racism, black and Hispanic women won elections in multiple states on Tuesday while Representative Steve King, a nine-term congressman with a long history of racist remarks, was ousted in a Republican primary in Iowa.

headline.main: Historic Wins for Women of Color as Nation Protests Systemic Racism
headline.print_headline: A Day of Historic Wins For Women of Color

byline.original: By Reid J. Epstein, Jennifer Medina and Nick Corasaniti

headline.print_headline: Joy. Hope.  And Then  A Graduate  Shot Dead.

docs.abstract: For Democratic city leaders across the country, the unrest in their streets is testing their campaign promises and principles.
docs.snippet: For Democratic city leaders across the country, the unrest in their streets is testing their campaign promises and principles.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — It’s a moment that mayors can still describe, months or years later. The first time they get the call: A police officer has killed someone, often that person is black or Latino, and a neighborhood is enraged.

headline.main: ‘Everybody Will Second-Guess’: Liberal Mayors Navigate Protesters and Police
headline.print_headline: Liberal Mayors Find Themselves Caught Between Protesters and the Police

docs.abstract: After more than 70 allegations surfaced on Twitter this weekend, gaming companies and streamers responded with action. Some say it’s the beginning of real change in the industry.
docs.snippet: After more than 70 allegations surfaced on Twitter this weekend, gaming companies and streamers responded with action. Some say it’s the beginning of real change in the industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than 70 people in the gaming industry, most of them women, have come forward with allegations of gender-based discrimination, harassment and sexual assault since Friday. They have shared their stories in statements posted to Twitter, YouTube, Twitch and the blogging platform TwitLonger.

headline.main: Dozens of Women in Gaming Speak Out About Sexism and Harassment
headline.print_headline: Female Gamers Tell of Sexism And Harassment

byline.original: By Taylor Lorenz and Kellen Browning

docs.abstract: Black leaders regularly fail to rise to the challenges that confront young people.
docs.snippet: Black leaders regularly fail to rise to the challenges that confront young people.
docs.lead_paragraph: Young black people have exploded in rebellion over the grotesque killing of George Floyd. We are now witnessing the broadest protest movement in American history. And yet the response of black elected officials has been cautious and uninspired.
